It is a good idea, I have a similar thing since long time. But my thing is in flat top surface. I scale in Z to get same heighth than the main print.<br />
Your "tree" has 2megabytes, quite a lot for a helper function. Helpers should be close as possible at printbed to the print because of oozing.<br />
My cool thing is Z=1mm, radius=1mm and I scale it in the slicing software to the needed size. STL is 4.9kb and available in a helper directory. Also there I have a cube.stl of 1mm and a cylinder. Maybe a (ABS) print needs a  raft layer so I scale in slicer the cube to 50,50,0.15 and set it to the same position as the print.<br />
//cool thing<br />
cylinder(1,0,1,$fn=6);<br />
cylinder(.2,.5,.2,$fn=6);
